examples.en: He was famed for his ruthlessness.
The famed faith healer turned out to be a charlatan.
The midlands of Tasmania are famed for their agricultural values.
The famed snows of Mount Kilimanjaro are receding, leaving behind much uncovered ground.
Every year raucous rubbernecks by the busload descend upon the city for its famed Mardi Gras.
Once famed as an actor, John Wilkes Booth is now remembered for a single exploit, his assassination of Lincoln.
